{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSPinCodeInput"}]}]},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"],"kind":"mentions"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Layouts","type":"heading","text":"Layouts"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"outlined","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" layout: A minimalist input with a transparent background and a visible stroke outlining the field."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This style may be interesting for contexts other than form pages, e.g. when inputs need to feel lightweight and unobtrusive,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in a header (search field), or in a selection\/filtering feature in a product catalog","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not outlined"}]},{"type":"text","text":" (default): An input with a subtle background fill and visible bottom border, creating a softer and more contained look."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Best suited for dense layouts or to enhance visibility."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component provides 3 layouts for the input: 4 boxes, 6 boxes or 8 boxes."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A helper text can be used to support text to convey additional information about the input field, such as how it will be used.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should ideally only take up a single line, though may wrap to multiple lines if required, and be either persistently visible or visible only on focus."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Error status","anchor":"Error-status","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Error status indicates that the user input does not meet validation rules or expected formatting."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides immediate visual feedback, typically through a red border, error icon, and a clear, accessible error message positioned below the input (mandatory)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This state helps users quickly identify and correct mistakes by explaining what went wrong and, when possible, how to fix it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The input remains editable, encouraging users to revise their input without starting over."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The error state must be triggered by an explicit validation (submission, API response), and not in real time with each keystroke."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This can occur either because the entered code does not match the expected code, because the user entered an expired or already used code,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or finally if the maximum number of attempts has been exceeded."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Specific-design-guidelines","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Specific design guidelines"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the context of a PIN code input, in addition to the input’s “Error” UI rendering, it is essential to also include an “Alert” component"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(also in its “Error” status) in the interface."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Particular cases","anchor":"Particular-cases"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput","isActive":true},{"text":" component supports autofill feature of values like OTP code.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example if the user receives a message with inside a code the system can extract, the keyboard can suggest to the user to fill it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If the digits fits the component, it will be filled."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the digits are longer, they will be truncated.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"If the digits are shorter, they will be filled, letting other fields empty."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The copy\/paste feature is also available and has the same behavior."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Technical considerations","anchor":"Technical-considerations","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For some cases, on phones screens or with 8 boxes in iPhone, you may need to use a "},{"code":"ScrollView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to embed the component and let user move it."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["ScrollView(.horizontal) {","    OUDSPinCodeInput($value,","                     length: .eight,","                     helperText: \"Enter your secret code sent to your phone\")","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note also the exposed ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"value"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding"},{"type":"text","text":" will be updated when all digits are written."}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","type":"heading","text":"Accessibility considerations"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The content of the fields is vocalized by Voice Over; the placeholders (defined in "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/obfuscationCharacter","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/placeholderCharacter","isActive":true},{"text":")","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are not vocalized to let users know what they wrote.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component gets only numeric values, not letters or symbols, only numbers."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Depending on the component configuration, autofocus can still be used when the component appears, and focus is moved to the next field as digits are entered."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For example if Voice Over is enavled, the autoficus is disabled."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component and its digit fields are vocalized with internal wording."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When using the error status, provide a clear, concise error message explaining what went wrong and, when possible, how to fix it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(for example: ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“The code you entered is invalid. Try again.”"}]},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use helper text to communicate additional guidance (for example: "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"“Check the 6‑digit code sent by SMS”"}]},{"type":"text","text":"), and keep this text short so it remains easy to vocalize"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and understand."}]},{"anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples","type":"heading","level":2},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ The value with the code","    @State private var pinCode: String = \"\"","","    \/\/ By default, the PIN code input displays only 6 boxes","    OUDSPinCodeInput($pinCode)","","    \/\/ It can have also up 4 or 8 boxes, with an helper text","    OUDSPinCodeInput($pinCode, length: .eight, helperText: \"Enter your 8 secret digits\")","","    \/\/ The component can be used in error contexts","    OUDSPinCodeInput($pinCode, length: .six, status: .error(message: \"The OTP code you entered is not correct\"))"],"type":"codeListing"},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","text":"Design documentation","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-pin-code-input"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Themes-rendering","text":"Themes rendering","level":2},{"text":"Orange","anchor":"Orange","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_pinCodeInput_Orange"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Orange Compact","level":3,"anchor":"Orange-Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_pinCodeInput_OrangeCompact"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Sosh","level":3,"anchor":"Sosh"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_pinCodeInput_Sosh"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Wireframe","level":3,"anchor":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_pinCodeInput_Wireframe"}]},{"name":"Version","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.2.0 (Figma component design version)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"Since","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1.4.0"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"PIN code input is a UI element that allows to capture short, fixed-length numeric codes, typically for authentication or confirmation purposes,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as a four, six or eight-digit personal identification number (PIN)."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"PIN code input is presented as a series of individual input fields or boxes, each representing a single digit, to enhance readability and encourage accurate input,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"while supporting smooth keyboard navigation and secured input masking if needed."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudspincodeinput"]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/init(_:length:helperText:isOutlined:status:autofocus:)","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/init(_:length:helperText:tableName:bundle:isOutlined:status:autofocus:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/body"],"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties"},{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/obfuscationCharacter","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/placeholderCharacter"],"title":"Type Properties","anchor":"Type-Properties"},{"generated":true,"anchor":"Enumerations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSPinCodeInput\/Length","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDS